name: 42-minishell
description: C, Unix system calls, Shell scripting. Developed a miniature shell in C, implementing a basic command-line interpreter. Features include parsing commands, handling environment variables, executing built-in and external commands, and supporting piping and redirections. Focused on process management and memory handling.

name: Jupyter-Python_Numpy_Fundamentals
description: This repository contains Jupyter Notebook files designed to learn the fundamentals of Python and the NumPy library. Each notebook focuses on step-by-step exercises covering topics such as data structures, loops, functions, arrays, and NumPy basics.

name: my_own_neural_networks
description: Building neural networks completely from scratch using only NumPy. Still in processing (hala geliştirme aşamasında...)— experimenting, optimizing, and learning the fundamentals step by step.

name: 42-push_swap
description: C Language. Developed sorting algorithms for stacks, optimizing for minimal operations. Learned algorithmic problem- solving and efficiency.

name: 42-fdf
description: C, MiniLibX, 2D/3D Graphics, Isometric Projection. Developed a 3D wireframe representation of maps using isometric projection. Implemented file parsing, coordinate transformation, and rendering of points and lines with the MiniLibX graphics library. Focused on graphical programming and coordinate system manipulation.

name: 42-piscine
description: A collection of solutions for 42 school piscine (bootcamp) exercises. Organized by subject and project, this repository showcases problem-solving skills, algorithmic thinking, and mastery of C programming concepts learned during the 42 curriculum

name: 42-get_next_line
description: C Language. Implemented a function to read a file descriptor line by line. Practiced dynamic memory allocation and buffer handling.

name: 42-ft_printf
description: C Language The standard printf function was reimplemented in C. Focus was placed on formatting and output management.

name: 42-libft
description: C Language A library of helper functions was developed in C by rewriting standard library functions.

name: 42-pipex
description: Pipex is a 42 school project that simulates the UNIX pipeline mechanism. It allows executing multiple commands connected via pipes, handling file redirections, and reproducing the behavior of shell pipelines. This project demonstrates mastery of process management, inter-process communication, and low-level system programming in C.

name: 42-philosophers
description: C Language. Implemented the dining philosophers problem using threads, mutexes, and semaphores. Focused on synchronization and concurrency.

name: Flutter-To_Do_List_App
description: To-Do List App, Flutter, Postman Cross-platform mobile app for managing daily tasks. Features: task creation, editing, deletion, and real-time synchronization.

name: Flutter-Music_Player_App
description: Experience your favorite music like never before with our sleek and intuitive Flutter Music Player App. Play, pause, and organize your songs effortlessly, create custom playlists, and enjoy high-quality audio with a modern, responsive interface. Built with Flutter for smooth performance on both Android and iOS.

name: SportFieldBookingSystem
description: This is an Java console based Sport Field Booking System. This is system provides maximum effiency for the user. While the implementation process, I used data structures such as LinkedList, Trees, Map...
